<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seela Truelight</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There is a nasty new bug introduced a couple of weeks ago with one of the recent patches that affects all forms of Resurrection. If the initial cast fails for some reason, or if the dialog box disappears without being answerered, the corpse becomes unressable as if the owner was not online, even if they are standing right in front of you. The only recourse is to have the player logout and back in again.<P>This can be bad if say, you have a naked player scouting in PoF with a corpse outside at the zone, and you suddenly find he is unressable when he gets aggroed. Even in non critical situations it is a nuisance, so I suggest you all submit /bug reports to help increase Verant's awareness of the problem.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Katandon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've heard of it happening to other Clerics on my server.  A few of the times they were standing right next to me complaining about it.<P>It's never happened to me, the most I've seen it occur is when there are multiple corpses and they are not being ressed in reverse order, i.e. the naked ones first.<P>As soon as I personally experience it I will file a bug however.<P>Cheers.<P>------------------<BR>Katandon Scarletrose<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KingHarald</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This happened to me last weekend.  I was called to revive a character.  He got the message stood up and the message disappeared.  I tried to revive again and got the message... I could not revive at this time, you may be able to later.  I had been reading the message boards, so I had him log off and back on.  I was able to revive him then.<P>Cindin<BR>Level 30</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tinymouse</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you want to reproduce this bug, all you have to do is lose focus on the "Do you want a rez" window. <P>For instance, I was looking through my inventory (using the "I" toggle) when a cleric rezzed me (with no warning, bad practice). I had to click out of the inventory window, which made the "Do you want a rez" window disappear. I suspect that the rez window was still there, just behind something (you couldn't see it of course). That might explain why you have to log out to get another rez cast (since the one is still 'waiting' for a yes or no).<P>------------------<BR>45th Cleric<BR>Companion's of the Gate<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Salina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Have had this happen about 3 times now.. it's *extremely* frustrating, especially with a group wipeout where every drop of mana is precious.<P>Logging out (and possibly zoning) seems to fix it.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
